<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,505,964]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Remarks.â€” 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[285,448,505,532]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref68457" refString="Distant, W. L. (1906) A synonymic catalogue of Homoptera. Part I. Cicadidae. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 207 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8554" type="book" year="1906">Distant (1906)</bibRefCitation>
revised the status of the species to a variety (currently a subspecies under the latest edition of the Code (ICZN 1999)) without comment in his synonymic catalogue. This may have been based on the fact that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanborn" authorityYear="2021" box="[201,320,578,603]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Yanga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angyrea" status="rev. stat.">
<emphasis box="[201,320,578,603]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Y. angyrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[328,431,577,603]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[328,431,577,603]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">rev. stat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Distant, 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[488,792,577,603]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Yanga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis box="[488,613,577,603]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Y. pulverea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[628,783,577,603]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="335 - 338" refId="ref67810" refString="Distant, W. L. (1882) Descriptions of a new species and a new genus of Cicadidae from Madagascar. Transaction of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 1882, 335 - 338, plate XV. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1882. tb 01579. x" type="journal article" year="1882">Distant, 1882</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
are the only known species of the genus to have hyaline hind wings. 
<bibRefCitation author="Melichar, L." box="[295,480,613,640]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="198 - 200" refId="ref69724" refString="Melichar, L. (1896) Eine neue Homopteren-art der gattung Platypleura Am. Serv. von Madagascar. Weiner Entomologische Zeitung, 15, 198 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 13874" type="journal article" year="1896">Melichar (1896)</bibRefCitation>
describes the species as having silver-gray marking on the fore wing and rounded male opercula while 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[388,513,649,675]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Yanga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis box="[388,513,649,675]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Y. pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the silver-gray marking on the fore wing, and has obliquely rounded lateral male opercula. In addition, 
<bibRefCitation author="Melichar, L." box="[463,646,685,712]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="198 - 200" refId="ref69724" refString="Melichar, L. (1896) Eine neue Homopteren-art der gattung Platypleura Am. Serv. von Madagascar. Weiner Entomologische Zeitung, 15, 198 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 13874" type="journal article" year="1896">Melichar (1896)</bibRefCitation>
listed the taxon as having a wingspan of 
<quantity box="[1117,1197,685,712]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="95.0">95 mm</quantity>
compared to the 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="105.0">105 mm</quantity>
listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[304,466,721,747]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="335 - 338" refId="ref67810" refString="Distant, W. L. (1882) Descriptions of a new species and a new genus of Cicadidae from Madagascar. Transaction of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 1882, 335 - 338, plate XV. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1882. tb 01579. x" type="journal article" year="1882">Distant (1882)</bibRefCitation>
for his species. Sanborn (2020) addressed a similar issue when 
<taxonomicName authority="(Butler, 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Pycna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[1179,1345,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Pycna angusta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Butler, A. G." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="388 - 389" refId="ref67654" refString="Butler, A. G. (1882) Description of two new species of the Homopterous genus Platypleura from Madagascar. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 5, 9, 388 - 389. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938209459056" type="journal article" year="1882">Butler, 1882</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was returned to species rank. Based on the size difference and the differences in the descriptions of the opercula the subspecies is returned to species status here to become 
<taxonomicName authority="(Melichar, 1896)" authorityName="Sanborn" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Melichar" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[864,1222,793,820]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Yanga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrea" status="rev. stat.">
<emphasis box="[864,1027,794,819]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Yanga argyrea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Melichar, L." box="[1041,1214,793,820]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="198 - 200" refId="ref69724" refString="Melichar, L. (1896) Eine neue Homopteren-art der gattung Platypleura Am. Serv. von Madagascar. Weiner Entomologische Zeitung, 15, 198 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 13874" type="journal article" year="1896">Melichar, 1896</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1229,1331,793,819]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1229,1331,793,819]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">rev. stat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,505,964]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanborn" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Melichar" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[199,364,830,855]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Yanga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrea" status="rev. stat.">
<emphasis box="[199,364,830,855]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Yanga argyrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[372,475,829,855]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[372,475,829,855]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">rev. stat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from all but 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[868,994,829,855]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Yanga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis box="[868,994,829,855]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Y. pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the hyaline hind wings. The silvergray marking on the fore wing, the rounded male opercula and smaller wingspan (
<quantity box="[1082,1164,865,892]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="95.0">95 mm</quantity>
) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanborn" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Melichar" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1212,1326,866,891]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Yanga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrea" status="rev. stat.">
<emphasis box="[1212,1326,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Y. argyrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1334,1436,865,891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1334,1436,865,891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">rev. stat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
distinguish it from 
<emphasis box="[365,497,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[365,493,901,927]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Yanga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">Y. pulverea</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,505,964]" box="[199,1066,937,964]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Distribution.â€”The species is only known from 
<collectingCountry box="[735,870,937,963]" name="Madagascar" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[885,1053,937,964]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref69829" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
